ists when this','line_number':22,'multiline':False]['text':' program terminates successfully.','line_number':23,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':24,'multiline':False]['text':' Some important details about the implementation of this program:','line_number':25,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':26,'multiline':False]['text':' * No threads to ensure the use of fork below does not cause trouble.','line_number':27,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':28,'multiline':False]['text':' * Pure C, no C++. This is intentional to keep the program low overhead','line_number':29,'multiline':False]['text':'   and to avoid the accidental introduction of heavy dependencies that','line_number':30,'multiline':False]['text':'   could spawn threads.','line_number':31,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':32,'multiline':False]['text':' * Error handling is extensive but there is no error propagation.  Given','line_number':33,'multiline':False]['text':'   that the goal of this program is just to spawn another one as a daemon,','line_number':34,'multiline':False]['text':'   we take the freedom to immediatey exit from anywhere as soon as we','line_number':35,'multiline':False]['text':'   hit an error.','line_number':36,'multiline':False]['text':' Configures std{in,out,err} of the current process to serve as a daemon.','line_number':52,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':53,'multiline':False]['text':' stdin is configured to read from /dev/null.','line_number':54,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':55,'multiline':False]['text':' stdout and stderr are configured to write to log_path, which is created and','line_number':56,'multiline':False]['text':' truncated unless log_append is set to true, in which case it is open for','line_number':57,'multiline':False]['text':' append if it exists.','line_number':58,'multiline':False]['text':' Writes the given pid to a new file at pid_path.','line_number':83,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':84,'multiline':False]['text':' Once the pid file has been created, this notifies pid_done_fd by writing a','line_number':85,'multiline':False]['text':' dummy character to it and closing it.','line_number':86,'multiline':False]['text':' Executes the requested binary configuring it to behave as a daemon.','line_number':117,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':118,'multiline':False]['text':' The stdout and stderr of the current process are redirected to the given','line_number':119,'multiline':False]['text':' log_path.  See SetupStdio for details on how this is handled.','line_number':120,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':121,'multiline':False]['text':' This blocks execution until pid_done_fd receives a write.  We do this','line_number':122,'multiline':False]['text':' because the Bazel server process (which is what we start with this helper','line_number':123,'multiline':False]['text':' binary) requires the PID file to be present at startup time so we must','line_number':124,'multiline':False]['text':' wait until the parent process has created it.','line_number':125,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':126,'multiline':False]['text':' This function never returns.','line_number':127,'multiline':False]['text':' Starts the given process as a daemon.','line_number':150,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':151,'multiline':False]['text':' This spawns a subprocess that will be configured to run the desired program','line_number':152,'multiline':False]['text':' as a daemon.  The program to run is supplied in exe and the arguments to it','line_number':153,'multiline':False]['text':' are given in the NULL-terminated argv.  argv[0] must be present and','line_number':154,'multiline':False]['text':' contain the program name (which may or may not match the basename of exe).','line_number':155,'multiline':False]['text':' NOLINT Unreachable.','line_number':171,'multiline':False]['text':' Program entry point.','line_number':178,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':179,'multiline':False]['text':' The primary responsibility of this function is to parse program options.','line_number':180,'multiline':False]['text':' Once that is done, delegates all work to Daemonize.','line_number':181,'multiline':False]